p: Ent-germacra-4(15),5,10(14)-trien-1β-ol, β–dictyopterol, and 3,5-di- O-caffeoyl quinic acid exhibited “moderate cytotoxicity” against five cancer cell lines, with ED 50 values varying between 1.52–18.57 μM (the most active–ED 50 between 1.52 and 18.57 μM–being β–dictyopterol) [ 49]. Methyl 3,5-dicaffeoyl quinate (MDQ) has demonstrated antioxidant activities, as well as antiproliferative effects in vitro, in HT-29 cell, by inducing cell cycle arrest and apoptosis through inhibition of the PI3K/Akt and ERK signaling pathways [ 156].
